HEADWORD: Embonpoint
<hw>Em`bon`point"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>en bon point</ets> in good condition. See <er>Bon</er>, and
<er>Point</er>.]</ety> <def>Plumpness of person; -- said especially of
persons somewhat corpulent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

